{"key":"post-10493157","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10493157</id>\n<content>There is no faster way to go from spores or culture to finished fruits than the brf/pf tek.&amp;nbsp; That's a fact.&amp;nbsp; Anyone who screws up the brf tek, or thinks it's a lot of work, should be ashamed to ever admit it in public.&amp;nbsp; It takes ten minutes to grind the rice into flour, mix the verm and water and load the jars.&amp;nbsp; It's totally foolproof.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Grains to bulk substrate will produce much more product, so once a person learns the ropes, they're the next logical step to take.&amp;nbsp; However, to ensure success, a pressure cooker and flow hood make a lot of sense, neither of which are required for the pf tek.&amp;nbsp; Thus, it's a great way for new growers to get started.&amp;nbsp; Many people get their first crop, eat it and get the living shit scared out of them and want no more part of mushrooms.&amp;nbsp; For them, it's good they didn't invest $500 or more into growing supplies, only to move on to something else a few weeks later.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10493190</next>\n<prev>10493119</prev>\n<first>10492614</first>\n<last>10524227</last>\n<when>1244817247</when>\n<utime>06/12/09 05:34 PM</utime>\n</post>"}